Independent audits of external debt registers of several African countries have revealed large hidden and unreported loans.Kenyans could be quite exposed and vulnerable to hidden external debts in our records as we do a very poor job at recording and reporting external debt data.  Parliament should demand a thorough and independent audit of our external debt register before approving any more increase to the public debt ceiling, now at Sh9 trillion.
The register is your single source of truth when you want to interrogate the integrity and accuracy of data and facts on the expensive foreign loans responsible for the runaway external debt situation we find ourselves in today.



